{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57eacff5-d947-4f39-a834-f6dc172c430c","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2** on .NET 9, you can use **constructor injection** for `TestContext` and combine `[TestInitialize]` for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor — TestContext is injected automatically\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous setup work here (e.g., simple assignments)\n    }\n\n    // Async init runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Test starting: \" + _testContext.TestName);\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.DisposeAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` via DI (MSTest 3.x+). Use for synchronous, lightweight setup.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — can return `Task` for async work. Runs *after* the constructor, before each test.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — use `static async Task` for one-time async class-level setup if needed.\n- Avoid putting async-over-sync (`.Result`/`.Wait()`) in the constructor; defer that to `[TestInitialize]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc830eae-bd9d-43e4-a331-118ecd8cf0e7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.2 targeting .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide guidance on the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+:\n1. You can inject `TestContext` via the constructor\n2. Use `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous per-test setup\n3. Use `[TestInitialize]` with async Task for asynchronous per-test setup\n4. Use `[ClassInitialize]` for one-time class-level setup\n\nThe modern approach with MSTest 3.x supports constructor injection of TestContext directly.","outputTokens":586,"requestId":"E3C3:2C57B5:66BC79:765017:6A05284D"},"id":"7dd1c450-cd52-4430-bd7c-e53facb00bc0","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:41:46.110Z","parentId":"5807cc41-b765-412b-a043-e54fb5e9cd89"}
